  "prompt": "How do you stop a Terrier/Border Collie mix from destroying your furniture?",
  "response": "To prevent a Terrier/Border Collie mix from destroying furniture, try these strategies:\n\n1. Exercise and Mental Stimulation\n- Provide plenty of daily exercise (at least 1-2 hours)\n- Use interactive toys and puzzle games\n- Engage in training and mental challenges\n\n2. Training\n- Teach basic obedience commands\n- Use positive reinforcement techniques\n- Provide consistent training and boundaries\n\n3. Chew Deterrents\n- Use bitter spray on furniture\n- Provide appropriate chew toys\n- Redirect chewing to acceptable items\n\n4. Crate Training\n- Use a crate when unsupervised\n- Make the crate comfortable and positive\n- Gradually increase crate time\n\n5. Reduce Boredom and Anxiety\n- Provide regular attention and interaction\n- Use calming aids like background music\n- Consider doggy daycare or dog walker\n\n6. Management Techniques\n- Block access to furniture when unsupervised\n- Use baby gates or closed doors\n- Keep valuable items out of reach\n\n7. Professional Help\n- Consider professional training\n- Consult a veterinarian about potential anxiety issues\n- Work with a dog behaviorist if problems persist\n\nConsistency and patience are key in addressing destructive behavior.",
